00:00:28.150 --> 00:00:32.740
"Who wants one more
American air base in the Persian Gulf?"

3
00:00:34.990 --> 00:00:36.820
"Who wants occupation by another name?"

4
00:00:38.950 --> 00:00:41.370
"Western imperialism by another name."

5
00:00:42.450 --> 00:00:44.620
"Who wants planes and helicopters

6
00:00:44.710 --> 00:00:46.000
flying over our children?"

7
00:00:46.960 --> 00:00:47.960
"Who wants to live

8
00:00:48.040 --> 00:00:49.040
- under a foreign flag."
- Okay.

9
00:00:49.130 --> 00:00:51.840
What have I missed?
What's the interpreter saying?

10
00:00:51.920 --> 00:00:53.260
So far pretty vanilla.

11
00:00:53.800 --> 00:00:55.800
- The usual grievances…
- "We will never accept…"

12
00:00:55.880 --> 00:00:56.930
DI Lenker?

13
00:00:57.510 --> 00:00:59.050
Bronze Command. what do you see?

14
00:00:59.140 --> 00:01:00.640
Yep. there's no problem on the ground.

15
00:01:00.720 --> 00:01:03.430
"This is the true face
of state-sponsored terrorism."

16
00:01:05.230 --> 00:01:07.310
"Let the occupiers pay
for the blood they shed."

17
00:01:07.400 --> 00:01:08.980
Okay. are you getting that?

18
00:01:09.650 --> 00:01:11.820
"Avenge this defilement
of a sovereign state."

19
00:01:12.360 --> 00:01:15.950
Cliff? You're the lawyer.
Anything we can charge?

20
00:01:16.030 --> 00:01:19.030
"Avenge" is not incitement
in and of itself. so…

21
00:01:22.200 --> 00:01:23.790
Gold Command. be advised.

22
00:01:23.870 --> 00:01:25.540
Counterprotest gathering
on Nailsworth Street.

23
00:01:30.170 --> 00:01:31.800
Okay. we knew this was coming.

24
00:01:32.420 --> 00:01:34.880
Unit C. hold them at the 80 yard cordon.

25
00:01:35.970 --> 00:01:37.720
Everyone else. eyes on the square.

26
00:01:39.890 --> 00:01:41.180
"An eye for an eye."

27
00:01:42.140 --> 00:01:43.310
"A life for a life."

28
00:01:43.390 --> 00:01:45.020
Right. does that clear the threshold?

29
00:01:45.600 --> 00:01:47.850
Death threat? Unlawful? Yes? No?

30
00:01:47.940 --> 00:01:50.480
The last time I checked. it wasn't
against the law to quote the Quran

31
00:01:50.560 --> 00:01:51.980
or indeed the Bible.

32
00:01:52.070 --> 00:01:54.440
- Cliff. no one likes a smart-arse.
- Well. I do.

33
00:01:55.740 --> 00:01:57.700
June. how we looking?

34
00:01:57.780 --> 00:01:59.990
Yeah. it's still pretty calm.
There's no physical threat.

35
00:02:00.070 --> 00:02:02.830
Okay. well.
discretion up to a point. yeah?

36
00:02:03.580 --> 00:02:06.000
"Let our vengeance be swift
and without mercy…"

37
00:02:06.080 --> 00:02:09.290
Unit Charlie to Gold Command.
we have 50 men at the outer cordon.

38
00:02:10.500 --> 00:02:13.250
Okay. but is the area secure?

39
00:02:13.340 --> 00:02:14.880
Secure for now. over.

40
00:02:16.090 --> 00:02:18.260
"Let these animals pay for their insult…"

41
00:02:18.340 --> 00:02:20.340
Well. that's not holy text surely.

42
00:02:20.430 --> 00:02:21.640
Right. so enough to arrest?

43
00:02:21.720 --> 00:02:26.430
It has to be a targeted threat against
a named individual or individuals.

44
00:02:26.520 --> 00:02:27.520
Oh. Cliff.

45
00:02:31.980 --> 00:02:34.610
Unit Charlie to Gold Command.
significant presence.

46
00:02:34.690 --> 00:02:37.440
75 meters down from the square.
it's getting pretty hot.

47
00:02:38.990 --> 00:02:40.320
That sounds close…

48
00:02:40.410 --> 00:02:43.280
Where is that? Is that Nailsworth Street?

49
00:02:47.040 --> 00:02:49.080
"Get organized.
Cut the head off the snake."

50
00:02:50.500 --> 00:02:51.540
Call to action?

51
00:02:51.630 --> 00:02:53.500
"Any American diplomats and apologists…"

52
00:02:53.590 --> 00:02:55.460
- Yes.
- Targeted call to violence?

53
00:02:55.550 --> 00:02:57.630
- Yes.
- Is that enough to escalate?

54
00:02:57.710 --> 00:02:58.720
I would say. "yes."

55
00:02:58.800 --> 00:03:00.630
Right. so we are clear to arrest?

56
00:03:00.720 --> 00:03:02.720
Section 44. You have grounds for arrest.

57
00:03:02.800 --> 00:03:04.640
Right. and is that your recommendation?

58
00:03:06.520 --> 00:03:08.390
Yep. yeah. Confirmed yes.

59
00:03:08.480 --> 00:03:10.560
Okay. And is it just the leader
or all of them?

60
00:03:10.640 --> 00:03:13.310
Because some of them are just…
Some of them are just kids.

61
00:03:14.480 --> 00:03:16.940
Hold it together!

62
00:03:17.780 --> 00:03:19.740
Let's go!

63
00:03:22.700 --> 00:03:23.700
Fuck!

64
00:03:23.780 --> 00:03:25.370
Urgent tactical support required. Repeat.

65
00:03:25.450 --> 00:03:27.330
- All… urgent…
- Recommend…

66
00:03:27.410 --> 00:03:30.710
Yeah. I'm sorry. ma'am. I can't…
I can't hear you. Can you repeat?

67
00:03:30.790 --> 00:03:33.040
Just the leader at present
so we can review the tapes…

68
00:03:33.130 --> 00:03:35.880
- Okay. You're clear to arrest the leader.
- Mike. Sierra. Mike. Sierra.

69
00:03:35.960 --> 00:03:37.090
Arrest authorized.

70
00:03:40.170 --> 00:03:42.760
Breach. breach!
They're heading towards the square!

71
00:03:57.900 --> 00:04:01.070
Urgent tactical support needed. All units…

72
00:04:01.900 --> 00:04:03.570
In! In. in. in!

73
00:04:03.660 --> 00:04:05.740
Break it up! Break it up!

74
00:04:20.260 --> 00:04:21.340
Get back!

75
00:04:23.760 --> 00:04:25.180
Get out the way!

76
00:04:38.940 --> 00:04:41.110
Help! Somebody. help!

77
00:04:43.240 --> 00:04:45.110
Out the way. Okay.

78
00:04:45.200 --> 00:04:46.490
Okay. Come here.

79
00:04:46.570 --> 00:04:47.780
Paramedics!

80
00:04:48.950 --> 00:04:50.200
You his friend. yeah?

81
00:04:50.290 --> 00:04:52.750
- You see here? Your hand here.
- Back. back! Everyone back!

82
00:04:52.830 --> 00:04:54.710
Press down hard. Look at me.
Press down hard.

83
00:04:55.870 --> 00:04:57.840
Okay. All right.

84
00:04:57.920 --> 00:04:59.750
Oh. my God. All right.

85
00:05:00.550 --> 00:05:02.710
Where are the paramedics?

86
00:05:05.300 --> 00:05:06.590
I've got you.

87
00:05:07.470 --> 00:05:10.470
All right. Look at me.
You're fine. I've got you.

88
00:05:12.140 --> 00:05:13.390
Mum.

89
00:05:13.480 --> 00:05:14.770
Mum.

90
00:05:15.440 --> 00:05:16.440
Mum.

91
00:05:16.520 --> 00:05:17.940
- I've got you. I've got you.
- Mum.

92
00:05:18.020 --> 00:05:19.440
You're gonna see your mum.

93
00:05:34.580 --> 00:05:38.210
When I think of you

94
00:05:41.420 --> 00:05:48.050
My heart remembers

95
00:05:49.550 --> 00:05:53.310
All the love we've ever had

96
00:05:53.390 --> 00:05:57.230
All the love we've ever had

97
00:05:57.810 --> 00:06:01.270
Just me and you

98
00:06:05.940 --> 00:06:09.410
When I think of you

99
00:06:13.160 --> 00:06:16.330
Just me and you

100
00:06:16.410 --> 00:06:20.380
Just me and you
Just me and you

101
00:06:25.880 --> 00:06:27.720
Thank you. Thank you. everybody.

102
00:06:27.800 --> 00:06:29.300
Please all take your seats.

103
00:06:29.380 --> 00:06:33.390
Before we begin. an urgent question
from Margo Whitaker. MP.

104
00:06:34.520 --> 00:06:36.730
Fifteen years old.

105
00:06:37.810 --> 00:06:41.480
Just a regular lad from my constituency.

106
00:06:42.610 --> 00:06:44.150
My backyard.

107
00:06:44.230 --> 00:06:46.190
- Cheers. mate.
- No worries.

108
00:06:48.700 --> 00:06:50.110
Hi. can I get a pen please?

109
00:06:50.990 --> 00:06:54.080
He only came along because. I quote.

110
00:06:54.160 --> 00:06:58.500
"There was room in the van.
and he wanted to go on the London Eye."

111
00:06:58.580 --> 00:07:03.130
Now. I see from the news
you are appealing for witnesses?

112
00:07:05.710 --> 00:07:06.710
Thanks.

113
00:07:06.800 --> 00:07:09.720
May I suggest you start with
the 34 officers stood around like lemmings

114
00:07:09.800 --> 00:07:11.510
whilst a boy was stabbed
to death in front of you?

115
00:07:11.590 --> 00:07:15.010
It's our understanding that
the Nailsworth Street rally

116
00:07:15.100 --> 00:07:17.060
was infiltrated at the 11th hour

117
00:07:17.140 --> 00:07:21.400
by a small cell
of up to six extremist individuals.

118
00:07:22.100 --> 00:07:23.860
Their faces covered.

119
00:07:23.940 --> 00:07:26.440
unknown to the others.
they came with the sole intention--

120
00:07:26.530 --> 00:07:30.610
Not one… Not one of this cell
have you been able to identify.

121
00:07:31.530 --> 00:07:36.370
Your job. last time I looked.
is to stop crime.

122
00:07:36.450 --> 00:07:41.790
And yet no arrests.
no witnesses and no murder weapon.

123
00:07:44.000 --> 00:07:47.380
Is it any wonder public confidence
in the police is rock bottom?

124
00:08:29.170 --> 00:08:30.840
Who is she. and what's she doing here?

125
00:08:31.340 --> 00:08:32.510
I'm…

126
00:08:34.010 --> 00:08:36.180
I just wanted to say.
I'm so sorry for your loss.

127
00:08:42.730 --> 00:08:43.770
He's saying.

128
00:08:45.100 --> 00:08:46.400
"What do you want?"

129
00:08:51.570 --> 00:08:52.740
I was with him. I was there.

130
00:08:53.700 --> 00:08:54.990
Your son.

131
00:08:55.950 --> 00:08:59.540
And I just… I wish I could've stopped it.

132
00:08:59.620 --> 00:09:00.830
Please go.

133
00:09:02.290 --> 00:09:04.080
Please. just someone make her go.

134
00:09:04.870 --> 00:09:06.330
It's okay.

135
00:09:06.420 --> 00:09:07.960
Sorry. I'm so sorry.

136
00:09:16.840 --> 00:09:18.680
- Can I have some?
- DI Lenker?

137
00:09:18.760 --> 00:09:20.640
Yeah. It's still pretty calm.
There's no physical threat.

138
00:09:20.720 --> 00:09:22.430
Urgent tactical support required. Repeat.

139
00:09:22.520 --> 00:09:24.640
All units.
urgent tactical support required.

140
00:09:24.730 --> 00:09:26.350
Where is that? Is that Nailsworth Street?

141
00:09:28.730 --> 00:09:30.690
- Mum.
- Where are the paramedics?

142
00:09:30.770 --> 00:09:32.820
Mum. Mum.

143
00:09:32.900 --> 00:09:35.110
- I've got you. I've got you.
- Mum.

144
00:10:06.140 --> 00:10:07.310
Thanks. Jerry.

145
00:10:16.200 --> 00:10:19.780
- Tony.
- Who are you?

146
00:10:20.910 --> 00:10:21.910
It's me.

147
00:10:22.950 --> 00:10:24.040
Dan. the gaffer.

148
00:10:26.120 --> 00:10:29.250
"The gaffer?" You sure? Fuckin' temerity.

149
00:10:29.330 --> 00:10:31.080
For Christ's sake. Tony.

150
00:10:33.210 --> 00:10:34.550
I'm not that far gone.

151
00:10:35.960 --> 00:10:37.550
Yeah. you should see old Jim
through the wall.

152
00:10:37.630 --> 00:10:39.380
He's on a drip and a respirator and…

153
00:10:40.720 --> 00:10:42.390
They still reckon he's a flight risk.

154
00:10:44.890 --> 00:10:47.140
You look like shit.
Don't tell me it's that daughter of yours.

155
00:10:47.230 --> 00:10:49.440
What's her name? Lulu or Louisa--

156
00:10:49.520 --> 00:10:50.900
- Lisa.
- Yeah. what's the latest?

157
00:10:50.980 --> 00:10:52.610
Is she still up north? Isle of…

158
00:10:52.690 --> 00:10:54.320
- Was it Isle of Eigg?
- Findhorn.

159
00:10:54.400 --> 00:10:56.360
Findhorn. Nice.

160
00:10:57.610 --> 00:11:00.780
Plenty of clapped-out old hippies
up there to keep her warm at night.

161
00:11:00.860 --> 00:11:01.870
Listen.

162
00:11:02.370 --> 00:11:04.240
I just wanted
to kick the tires on something.

163
00:11:04.950 --> 00:11:06.620
Here it comes. The ulterior motive.

164
00:11:06.700 --> 00:11:07.750
Yeah. Crack on.

165
00:11:07.830 --> 00:11:10.920
Something you said a while back.

166
00:11:11.000 --> 00:11:12.000
What did I say?

167
00:11:13.130 --> 00:11:14.130
This guy.

168
00:11:15.050 --> 00:11:16.800
Cosmo Thompson.

169
00:11:19.340 --> 00:11:20.340
I see.

170
00:11:21.300 --> 00:11:23.050
You said he was nothing. Small time.

171
00:11:23.140 --> 00:11:24.140
Yeah.

172
00:11:25.100 --> 00:11:26.390
Well. I changed my mind.

173
00:11:32.520 --> 00:11:35.770
Now. I gather you're keen
to help with the investigation.

174
00:11:35.860 --> 00:11:38.070
Well. I was there.
So. yeah. of course I want to help.

175
00:11:38.150 --> 00:11:41.320
Well. Mike and his team downstairs
are more than competent

176
00:11:41.410 --> 00:11:43.320
- to handle things. Okay?
- I'm not saying they're not.

177
00:11:43.410 --> 00:11:45.700
They don't need you
marking their homework for them.

178
00:11:45.780 --> 00:11:47.540
But you've got
a lot of friends here. June.

179
00:11:47.620 --> 00:11:50.160
so no one's throwing you to the wolves.
Not while I'm here.

180
00:11:50.960 --> 00:11:51.960
Let me tell you.

181
00:11:52.040 --> 00:11:55.590
the person responsible
for the death of that lad

182
00:11:55.670 --> 00:11:59.210
is the individual who stuck
a six-inch blade in his chest.

183
00:11:59.920 --> 00:12:01.510
And whoever that is. we will run 'em down.

184
00:12:01.590 --> 00:12:05.100
And when we do.
all this name-calling and finger-jabbing.

185
00:12:05.720 --> 00:12:06.970
it'll come to an end. Okay?

186
00:12:07.060 --> 00:12:09.730
But until then.
we've just gotta put up with it.

187
00:12:09.810 --> 00:12:11.940
- So leave Mike and his team to it. yeah?
- Yeah.

188
00:12:12.480 --> 00:12:14.230
- Yeah?
- Yes.

189
00:12:14.310 --> 00:12:16.770
Good. That's pep talk over.

190
00:12:19.740 --> 00:12:21.240
In the meantime.

191
00:12:21.320 --> 00:12:23.660
no further contact
with the victim's family. I would--

192
00:12:23.740 --> 00:12:25.450
Sorry. Can I ask why?

193
00:12:25.530 --> 00:12:28.450
- Just erring on the side of…
- Caution?

194
00:12:28.540 --> 00:12:29.660
Right.

195
00:12:30.290 --> 00:12:32.580
So give your statement and move on. okay?

196
00:12:33.080 --> 00:12:35.540
I want you kept well away
from the blast radius.

197
00:12:35.630 --> 00:12:36.960
Okay.

198
00:12:37.040 --> 00:12:38.050
Very good.

199
00:12:44.800 --> 00:12:45.800
Here you go.

200
00:12:45.890 --> 00:12:47.220
Okay. picture round.

201
00:12:58.150 --> 00:13:00.150
- Is this all you've got?
- Afraid so.

202
00:13:00.780 --> 00:13:02.610
Waiting on CCTV analysis.

203
00:13:04.240 --> 00:13:06.820
Plenty of witnesses. but nothing of value.

204
00:13:23.840 --> 00:13:25.260
Can I take this one?

205
00:13:54.710 --> 00:13:56.870
It's three days since violence erupted

206
00:13:56.960 --> 00:13:59.080
at Suffolk Square in Central London.

207
00:13:59.170 --> 00:14:02.670
causing the death of a teenage boy
as well as countless injuries.

208
00:14:02.750 --> 00:14:05.920
Tonight. we ask what the police
could have done differently.

209
00:14:06.010 --> 00:14:10.260
and whether it's time to start treating
homegrown extremists as terrorists.

210
00:14:34.450 --> 00:14:37.290
Billy Fielding arrived
in court. where he was sentenced

211
00:14:37.370 --> 00:14:40.670
to 17 years for killing his girlfriend.
Cerys Jones.

212
00:14:41.960 --> 00:14:46.340
A statement was read outside
on behalf of Cerys's mother. Ashley Jones.

213
00:14:46.420 --> 00:14:50.050
While today's judgment
goes some way to bring justice

214
00:14:50.140 --> 00:14:52.930
for the murder of my daughter. Cerys.

215
00:14:53.850 --> 00:14:56.430
there is nothing that
can ever bring her back

216
00:14:56.520 --> 00:14:59.310
or make up for her loss from this world.

217
00:14:59.980 --> 00:15:02.650
Cerys was 16 years old.

218
00:15:02.730 --> 00:15:05.360
She had her whole life in front of her.

219
00:15:05.440 --> 00:15:09.200
Every day I have to
remind myself she is gone.

220
00:15:43.400 --> 00:15:44.480
Ashley?

221
00:15:45.860 --> 00:15:47.320
Ashley Jones?

222
00:15:47.400 --> 00:15:50.070
This is DI June Lenker.
Can you open the door please?

223
00:15:56.120 --> 00:15:57.120
Okay.

224
00:15:58.290 --> 00:15:59.290
All right.

225
00:16:01.080 --> 00:16:02.080
Ashley.

226
00:16:15.600 --> 00:16:16.680
Ashley?

227
00:16:28.190 --> 00:16:29.190
Hello?

228
00:16:30.740 --> 00:16:31.740
Ashley?

229
00:16:32.910 --> 00:16:35.370
Ashley? Ashley?

230
00:16:37.490 --> 00:16:38.540
Can you hear me?

231
00:16:39.040 --> 00:16:40.700
Hello. Ashley?

232
00:16:41.790 --> 00:16:43.870
Hi. yeah. I need an ambulance.

233
00:16:43.960 --> 00:16:45.960
I've got an unresponsive female.

234
00:16:46.040 --> 00:16:47.710
It's 20 Westview Court off Dalston Lane.

235
00:16:48.710 --> 00:16:49.710
Oh. hang on.

236
00:16:49.800 --> 00:16:51.800
No. Fine. Cancel.

237
00:16:52.510 --> 00:16:53.510
You okay?

238
00:16:57.640 --> 00:16:58.640
Okay.

239
00:17:00.520 --> 00:17:02.430
Yeah. sorry about that.

240
00:17:02.520 --> 00:17:05.150
Ashley. have you swallowed anything else
apart from the metapotrozine?

241
00:17:05.690 --> 00:17:06.810
- No.
- No?

242
00:17:06.900 --> 00:17:09.820
- Sorry. It's just…
- That's okay.

243
00:17:09.900 --> 00:17:11.780
It calms me down. You know?

244
00:17:11.860 --> 00:17:13.900
Yeah. All right. Let's…

245
00:17:14.780 --> 00:17:16.450
Should we get you some help?

246
00:17:16.530 --> 00:17:19.030
Yeah. I was gonna have a bath though.

247
00:17:20.160 --> 00:17:21.160
Yeah.

248
00:18:01.330 --> 00:18:02.830
Lovely pull. that.

249
00:18:02.910 --> 00:18:04.580
- You know I don't like this flavor.
- Go on. Cosmo.

250
00:18:04.660 --> 00:18:06.040
- Is it hot?
- Stick it down his…

251
00:18:06.120 --> 00:18:08.210
- Is it a bit hot? Is it a bit hot?
- Will you stop…

252
00:18:11.750 --> 00:18:13.550
Give me some good news for Christ's sake.

253
00:18:13.630 --> 00:18:15.010
No such luck.

254
00:18:15.550 --> 00:18:17.050
Three guesses what I'm looking at.

255
00:18:17.130 --> 00:18:19.140
- Go on.
- Give us a clue.

256
00:18:19.220 --> 00:18:20.510
It's mad.

257
00:18:20.600 --> 00:18:21.760
That's not a clue.

258
00:18:21.850 --> 00:18:23.220
All right. then. It's a…

259
00:18:23.310 --> 00:18:25.100
It's a blast from the past.

260
00:18:25.850 --> 00:18:27.230
That narrows it down a bit.

261
00:18:32.900 --> 00:18:34.690
You are gonna love this.

262
00:18:51.340 --> 00:18:52.670
You all right back there?

263
00:18:53.170 --> 00:18:54.670
Dunno.

264
00:18:55.340 --> 00:18:57.260
You sure you don't want
to sit up front with me?

265
00:18:57.970 --> 00:18:58.970
No.

266
00:19:02.850 --> 00:19:04.310
So. Leo DiCaprio. eh?

267
00:19:04.970 --> 00:19:06.180
You a big fan?

268
00:19:07.230 --> 00:19:08.520
I love him.

269
00:19:09.310 --> 00:19:10.310
Okay.

270
00:19:11.900 --> 00:19:12.980
Kidding.

271
00:19:13.070 --> 00:19:14.230
I'm kidding.

272
00:19:15.150 --> 00:19:18.820
I mean. don't get me wrong.
I used to fancy him. but nowadays I dunno.

273
00:19:19.360 --> 00:19:21.410
I think he's got a bit fat. to be honest.

274
00:19:21.490 --> 00:19:23.620
Oh. well. Try to let him down gently. eh?

275
00:19:24.370 --> 00:19:26.500
They can be a touchy lot.
these film stars.

276
00:19:32.500 --> 00:19:33.590
Do you remember me?

277
00:19:34.880 --> 00:19:36.880
'Course. That refuge.

278
00:19:36.960 --> 00:19:38.470
Carmichael Street.

279
00:19:38.550 --> 00:19:39.550
Yeah. that's it.

280
00:19:39.630 --> 00:19:42.180
Shame. That was…
They were nice. Nice people.

281
00:19:42.970 --> 00:19:43.970
Yeah. they were.

282
00:19:46.010 --> 00:19:47.100
So. what do you want?

283
00:19:48.520 --> 00:19:49.690
Me?

284
00:19:49.770 --> 00:19:52.900
Oh. I just thought I'd look in on you
after all these years.

285
00:19:55.150 --> 00:19:56.440
That's sweet.

286
00:20:13.000 --> 00:20:14.250
How long has it been?

287
00:20:15.170 --> 00:20:16.420
Since Cerys?

288
00:20:17.880 --> 00:20:18.920
Six years.

289
00:20:20.130 --> 00:20:21.970
Wow. Can't believe that.

290
00:20:23.680 --> 00:20:24.800
I still talk to her.

291
00:20:26.760 --> 00:20:27.930
Yeah?

292
00:20:28.680 --> 00:20:29.680
Every day.

293
00:20:32.060 --> 00:20:33.060
That's good.

294
00:20:38.820 --> 00:20:39.990
And the boy that…

295
00:20:41.030 --> 00:20:43.700
Do you… Do you know where they put him?
Whitecross. was it?

296
00:20:45.410 --> 00:20:46.410
Redheath.

297
00:20:47.200 --> 00:20:48.200
Redheath.

298
00:20:50.080 --> 00:20:51.330
And is he…

299
00:20:52.580 --> 00:20:53.960
Is he still in there? Do you know?

300
00:20:54.040 --> 00:20:55.880
- Stop the car.
- What?

301
00:20:55.960 --> 00:20:58.920
- Stop the car. Stop the car. Stop--
- Okay. All right.

302
00:21:00.840 --> 00:21:01.840
Okay?

303
00:21:04.550 --> 00:21:08.310
- I'm sick. I ain't stupid.
- Yeah. I know. I know.

304
00:21:09.640 --> 00:21:11.060
What is it you want to say to me?

305
00:21:11.140 --> 00:21:12.270
Nothing. Nothing.

306
00:21:12.350 --> 00:21:14.560
I was… I was just… I was just checking in.

307
00:21:15.730 --> 00:21:17.980
'Cause you know what they called it.
the judge and that?

308
00:21:18.610 --> 00:21:21.240
"An act of cold-blooded. callous cruelty."

309
00:21:21.320 --> 00:21:23.900
- I know.
- "Callous cruelty."

310
00:21:23.990 --> 00:21:25.070
I know.

311
00:21:25.860 --> 00:21:27.740
She was my daughter.

312
00:21:28.450 --> 00:21:30.740
- She was my only child.
- I know.

313
00:21:30.830 --> 00:21:33.790
And as far as I'm concerned.
he can fucking well die in there.

314
00:21:33.870 --> 00:21:35.250
So. last chance. yeah.

315
00:21:35.830 --> 00:21:37.460
What is it you want to say?

316
00:21:41.260 --> 00:21:42.380
Nothing.

317
00:21:45.340 --> 00:21:46.340
Nothing.

318
00:21:47.640 --> 00:21:49.680
I'm so sorry. I didn't mean to scare you.

319
00:21:51.770 --> 00:21:52.810
Okay?

320
00:21:54.600 --> 00:21:55.850
It's okay.

321
00:21:57.730 --> 00:21:58.900
Come on. then.

322
00:21:59.520 --> 00:22:02.570
Let's get over there quick
before they close the kitchen.

323
00:22:12.450 --> 00:22:14.450
Okay. You take your time. Yeah?

324
00:22:17.830 --> 00:22:20.170
Hiya. DI Lenker. I called.

325
00:22:20.920 --> 00:22:23.460
- This is Ashley.
- Come on. Ashley.

326
00:22:23.550 --> 00:22:25.760
This way. There you go. Just here.

327
00:22:30.180 --> 00:22:31.260
June.

328
00:22:32.760 --> 00:22:34.680
"I'm king of the world!"

329
00:22:36.140 --> 00:22:37.600
Come and see me.

330
00:23:31.320 --> 00:23:33.740
- Hello. Redheath.
- Hi. this is DI June Lenker.

331
00:23:33.830 --> 00:23:35.450
Dalston Lane CID.

332
00:23:35.540 --> 00:23:36.910
Hi. How can I help?

333
00:23:37.000 --> 00:23:40.620
I want to put in a visiting request
for a Billy Fielding.

334
00:23:41.210 --> 00:23:44.960
It's prisoner number
Alpha-3-7-Charlie-November.

335
00:23:45.920 --> 00:23:47.420
I'm going to give you a different number.

336
00:23:50.590 --> 00:23:53.350
Hi. this is Brian Teller.
Acting Custodial Manager.

337
00:23:53.430 --> 00:23:56.060
I gather you're inquiring
about an inmate here at Redheath?

338
00:23:56.140 --> 00:23:57.770
Yeah. Billy Fielding.

339
00:23:57.850 --> 00:24:00.520
Right. and you wish
to submit a visit order?

340
00:24:00.600 --> 00:24:03.480
Yeah. In fact it should be
in your colleague's inbox now.

341
00:24:03.560 --> 00:24:04.900
I've literally just sent it over.

342
00:24:06.400 --> 00:24:08.530
I'm afraid a visit
won't be possible at this point.

343
00:24:08.610 --> 00:24:09.860
Why not?

344
00:24:09.950 --> 00:24:12.820
Okay. Let me stop you right there.
This is Graeme. the Governor's assistant.

345
00:24:12.910 --> 00:24:14.490
I'm afraid that inmate is no longer here.

346
00:24:16.200 --> 00:24:17.200
Sorry?

347
00:24:17.290 --> 00:24:18.910
He's been transferred to another prison.

348
00:24:19.000 --> 00:24:20.000
Transferred?

349
00:24:20.080 --> 00:24:21.170
That's correct.

350
00:24:21.920 --> 00:24:24.630
Why… Why isn't this on the system?

351
00:24:24.710 --> 00:24:25.960
Where is he?

352
00:24:26.040 --> 00:24:28.550
I'm afraid we're not at liberty
to share that information.

353
00:24:28.630 --> 00:24:31.220
- Why not?
- Basically. it's a safeguarding issue.

354
00:24:31.300 --> 00:24:33.510
"Safeguarding"? Wow. Okay.

355
00:24:33.590 --> 00:24:34.600
That's a…

356
00:24:35.720 --> 00:24:36.810
That's a new one.

357
00:24:37.350 --> 00:24:38.350
Look…

358
00:24:40.020 --> 00:24:42.230
Could you just please
just tell me where he is?

359
00:24:42.730 --> 00:24:46.230
Here's what we can do.
Why don't you give me your number?

360
00:24:46.320 --> 00:24:48.650
And I'll call you as soon
as I have more information.

361
00:24:54.530 --> 00:24:57.530
- Graeme.
- Dan. do you have a minute?

362
00:25:01.330 --> 00:25:03.210
You… Are you okay
to do this. with everything?

363
00:25:03.290 --> 00:25:04.290
Yeah.

364
00:25:05.250 --> 00:25:08.800
You sure? 'Cause we can reschedule
if you like. you know?

365
00:25:08.880 --> 00:25:10.760
Yeah. I want to get my money's worth.

366
00:25:10.840 --> 00:25:12.260
What's with the…

367
00:25:13.010 --> 00:25:14.720
- Why are you all dressed up?
- What?

368
00:25:15.300 --> 00:25:16.390
Am I meant to be dressed up?

369
00:25:16.470 --> 00:25:17.720
What? Like date night?

370
00:25:18.310 --> 00:25:19.680
Yeah. date night for screwups.

371
00:25:22.770 --> 00:25:24.520
Oh. come on.
It's your favorite hour of the week.

372
00:25:39.370 --> 00:25:40.410
Hi.

373
00:25:42.120 --> 00:25:43.370
So…

374
00:25:44.460 --> 00:25:46.080
how have we been getting on?

375
00:25:48.170 --> 00:25:49.420
Who wants to start?

376
00:25:55.260 --> 00:25:56.680
That was good. wasn't it?

377
00:25:58.350 --> 00:25:59.350
Useful.

378
00:26:00.260 --> 00:26:02.520
Safety valve or… or whatever.

379
00:26:03.600 --> 00:26:04.600
Oh. shut up.

380
00:26:05.940 --> 00:26:06.940
What?

381
00:26:07.650 --> 00:26:08.730
You fancy her.

382
00:26:10.690 --> 00:26:12.110
Who? What? Maggie?

383
00:26:12.190 --> 00:26:14.070
Oh. Maggie. Maggie.

384
00:26:14.150 --> 00:26:16.320
- Fragrant Maggie.
- "Fragrant."

385
00:26:16.410 --> 00:26:18.570
- I don't… I don't blame you. you know?
- I mean. what?

386
00:26:18.660 --> 00:26:19.780
She's…

387
00:26:19.870 --> 00:26:22.450
She's like Yoda with amazing hair.

388
00:26:22.540 --> 00:26:23.830
Well. yeah.

389
00:26:23.910 --> 00:26:26.080
I guess. if you're gonna put it like that…

390
00:26:26.170 --> 00:26:27.920
- So predictable.
- …then maybe I do.

391
00:26:30.460 --> 00:26:32.590
I was thinking maybe we could
do something tonight.

392
00:26:34.210 --> 00:26:35.590
Jacob's with his dad.

393
00:26:37.130 --> 00:26:39.430
- Oh. yeah. Like what?
- Cheap night in?

394
00:26:40.970 --> 00:26:42.180
Ever the romantic.

395
00:26:42.260 --> 00:26:43.520
Or. I don't know. we could…

396
00:26:44.640 --> 00:26:47.730
get a drink. go to a bar. People watch.

397
00:26:50.230 --> 00:26:51.270
June?

398
00:26:54.030 --> 00:26:55.280
June. you okay?

399
00:26:56.150 --> 00:26:57.150
Yeah.

400
00:26:58.610 --> 00:26:59.870
just give me a minute.

401
00:27:23.680 --> 00:27:25.020
I'm sorry about your trouble.

402
00:27:25.770 --> 00:27:26.770
My what?

403
00:27:26.850 --> 00:27:28.770
First time as SIO in the wild.

404
00:27:29.520 --> 00:27:32.020
Leading the line against
a crowd of headbangers.

405
00:27:32.110 --> 00:27:33.570
Not quite the first time. but…

406
00:27:34.150 --> 00:27:36.240
It's tough. Tough going.

407
00:27:36.320 --> 00:27:38.110
Sorry. I'm not meaning
to pick at your scabs.

408
00:27:38.200 --> 00:27:39.570
- Sure.
- You're okay though?

409
00:27:40.610 --> 00:27:41.620
Yeah.

410
00:27:42.530 --> 00:27:43.910
How about you? You all right?

411
00:27:43.990 --> 00:27:44.990
Yeah.

412
00:27:45.540 --> 00:27:47.910
Same old. you know.
Eighth floor looking after you?

413
00:27:49.160 --> 00:27:50.790
They're being pretty supportive. actually.

414
00:27:50.870 --> 00:27:52.250
Good.

415
00:27:52.330 --> 00:27:55.920
It's good to hear.
Least they can do under the circumstances.

416
00:27:56.960 --> 00:27:57.970
What does that mean?

417
00:27:58.050 --> 00:27:59.590
Zero planning.

418
00:28:00.340 --> 00:28:04.390
Tactical balls up. Political pressure.
no doubt. but that's on them…

419
00:28:05.350 --> 00:28:06.970
- Yeah.
- …not you.

420
00:28:10.230 --> 00:28:11.480
Well. thanks for that.

421
00:28:13.270 --> 00:28:14.270
So…

422
00:28:16.360 --> 00:28:17.440
This guy. Billy Fielding.

423
00:28:20.780 --> 00:28:21.780
Oh. right.

424
00:28:22.360 --> 00:28:24.490
It's work. It's not personal.

425
00:28:25.240 --> 00:28:27.700
- I heard you retired.
- Nah. where would I go?

426
00:28:29.710 --> 00:28:31.040
No. they moved me

427
00:28:32.370 --> 00:28:33.790
to Intelligence.

428
00:28:36.170 --> 00:28:37.880
So I'm just asking for a friend.

429
00:28:40.010 --> 00:28:41.380
What's your interest?

430
00:28:42.300 --> 00:28:43.470
"My interest"?

431
00:28:45.050 --> 00:28:48.060
Well. I suppose
my first question would be.

432
00:28:48.140 --> 00:28:51.640
"Since when were the Prison Service
such fucking terrible liars?"

433
00:28:53.230 --> 00:28:55.900
Where is he? Fielding? Is he out?

434
00:28:56.690 --> 00:28:57.940
What's on your mind?

435
00:29:06.070 --> 00:29:07.870
- Suffolk Square.
- Your thing?

436
00:29:07.950 --> 00:29:10.330
- My thing.
- No prizes for best photographer.

437
00:29:10.410 --> 00:29:13.370
Look. if you're just gonna sit there
and deny it… I was there.

438
00:29:13.460 --> 00:29:14.630
So. I saw him.

439
00:29:14.710 --> 00:29:15.920
You saw him?

440
00:29:17.130 --> 00:29:18.800
- Yeah.
- And have you told Mike

441
00:29:18.880 --> 00:29:19.880
about this notion?

442
00:29:19.960 --> 00:29:22.170
- "Notion"?
- Or anyone else on his team?

443
00:29:22.260 --> 00:29:23.300
Did you. June. did you?

444
00:29:23.380 --> 00:29:24.970
No. Not yet. Why?

445
00:29:30.270 --> 00:29:31.270
What's going on here?

446
00:29:42.740 --> 00:29:44.950
You'll find these are a better angle.

447
00:30:06.300 --> 00:30:07.300
So. it is him?

448
00:30:08.800 --> 00:30:09.890
It's him?

449
00:30:11.600 --> 00:30:14.350
- But how… How… How is he even…
- He broke out.

450
00:30:14.980 --> 00:30:15.980
Friday night.

451
00:30:16.480 --> 00:30:18.730
Catering truck exits through the gates.

452
00:30:18.810 --> 00:30:21.400
security's short-staffed
so nobody checked underneath.

453
00:30:21.480 --> 00:30:22.820
Can you believe?

454
00:30:22.900 --> 00:30:26.070
- He was hiding under the truck?
- God bless the Prison Service.

455
00:30:27.360 --> 00:30:28.990
Why isn't this on the news?

456
00:30:31.620 --> 00:30:32.740
Circle of trust?

457
00:30:35.500 --> 00:30:36.500
Think about it.

458
00:30:36.580 --> 00:30:40.340
Prison staff report he's gone
early hours of Saturday morning.

459
00:30:40.420 --> 00:30:41.960
A few hours back and forth.

460
00:30:42.050 --> 00:30:45.010
Panic. Blame game. The police think
they've got him. "Oh. no. We haven't."

461
00:30:45.090 --> 00:30:48.390
They're finally putting a statement
together when your thing happened.

462
00:30:48.470 --> 00:30:49.760
Suffolk Square.

463
00:30:50.680 --> 00:30:52.470
And. you know.
the view from the politburo is…

464
00:30:52.560 --> 00:30:54.140
- Two stories?
- Same weekend.

465
00:30:54.220 --> 00:30:55.770
A prison break and a stabbing?

466
00:30:55.850 --> 00:30:57.020
Institutionally. it's…

467
00:30:57.100 --> 00:31:00.110
- Unsurvivable.
- Tough. Yeah. maybe so.

468
00:31:00.730 --> 00:31:03.980
Plus. of course. there's. "Fingers crossed
we get him quick. No one's any the wiser."

469
00:31:05.900 --> 00:31:07.860
What are we on now? Day four?

470
00:31:08.660 --> 00:31:09.660
Five.

471
00:31:11.070 --> 00:31:15.370
So. I've been wheeled in
for analytic support.

472
00:31:16.040 --> 00:31:17.460
Always a desperate sign.

473
00:31:18.870 --> 00:31:22.380
But if he's on the run.
what is he doing in the center of a riot?

474
00:31:28.880 --> 00:31:30.220
Why are you telling me all this?

475
00:31:33.180 --> 00:31:36.390
Well. we're in the same boat.

476
00:31:37.890 --> 00:31:39.350
Same interest. This guy here.

477
00:31:39.940 --> 00:31:41.770
He's a key witness for your murder.

478
00:31:41.860 --> 00:31:44.230
And. as for me.
I just want him back where he belongs.

479
00:31:44.980 --> 00:31:46.030
In prison?

480
00:31:46.110 --> 00:31:47.150
Aye.

481
00:31:49.530 --> 00:31:50.530
And that's it?

482
00:31:53.120 --> 00:31:55.330
My point is. if this thing gets out.

483
00:31:55.410 --> 00:31:58.160
Mike. investigation. public appeal.

484
00:31:58.250 --> 00:32:00.580
Billy Fielding goes to ground.
we'll never get him.

485
00:32:03.340 --> 00:32:04.340
So…

486
00:32:06.340 --> 00:32:07.340
you help me.

487
00:32:08.300 --> 00:32:09.340
I mean it.

488
00:32:09.420 --> 00:32:11.470
You help me run him down.

489
00:32:11.550 --> 00:32:12.800
We do it our way.

490
00:32:12.890 --> 00:32:15.060
And when we do. you talk to him.

491
00:32:15.140 --> 00:32:17.310
Interview. Suffolk Square.

492
00:32:17.390 --> 00:32:19.390
What was he doing there? Was he armed?

493
00:32:19.480 --> 00:32:21.810
Who was he with? Names. faces.

494
00:32:23.480 --> 00:32:25.400
You want me to work for you?

495
00:32:26.440 --> 00:32:27.650
Change of scene.

496
00:32:28.490 --> 00:32:30.280
You make it sound like a mini-break.

497
00:32:30.990 --> 00:32:31.990
No.

498
00:32:32.610 --> 00:32:34.280
It's better than a mini-break.

499
00:32:42.580 --> 00:32:44.420
Are you fucking shitting me?

500
00:32:44.500 --> 00:32:45.670
Hegarty?

501
00:32:45.750 --> 00:32:49.840
- Look. maybe this is what I need?
- "What you need"? That twat? No. no.

502
00:32:50.380 --> 00:32:54.390
- Self-help is not a good look on you.
- I knew you were gonna be like this.

503
00:32:55.600 --> 00:32:56.600
Yeah.

504
00:32:56.680 --> 00:32:59.350
'Cause I've got an actual brain.
More or less.

505
00:32:59.430 --> 00:33:00.980
What's Leo got to say about all this?

506
00:33:01.770 --> 00:33:03.310
Well. I…

507
00:33:05.150 --> 00:33:06.150
Of course.

508
00:33:06.230 --> 00:33:10.820
- You haven't told him. Nice.
- No. I will… I will tell him.

509
00:33:10.900 --> 00:33:12.950
- Right.
- It's just… What?

510
00:33:13.030 --> 00:33:16.200
No. Nothing. Just…
Just looking out for my psycho friend.

511
00:33:16.280 --> 00:33:17.530
Then stop yelling at her.

512
00:33:22.870 --> 00:33:26.670
- What you doing?
- I'm… I'm driving. I'm making it last.

513
00:33:28.000 --> 00:33:29.000
Right. Listen.

514
00:33:29.090 --> 00:33:31.220
There's something I've gotta say.
so I'm just gonna say it.

515
00:33:31.300 --> 00:33:33.800
Oh. I'm getting weirdly nervous now.

516
00:33:34.760 --> 00:33:36.970
What happened at Suffolk Square…

517
00:33:39.100 --> 00:33:40.350
it made me so angry.

518
00:33:40.430 --> 00:33:45.310
It was a fucking disgrace.
but it is not your disgrace.

519
00:33:53.360 --> 00:33:54.450
Oi.

520
00:33:54.950 --> 00:33:55.990
What?

521
00:33:57.120 --> 00:33:58.240
Got a bit going on?

522
00:34:00.330 --> 00:34:01.330
Yeah.

523
00:34:02.870 --> 00:34:03.870
Yeah.

524
00:34:06.540 --> 00:34:08.000
It's just…

525
00:34:08.090 --> 00:34:09.090
Yeah.

526
00:34:09.710 --> 00:34:11.340
- I know--
- No. you don't know.

527
00:34:15.930 --> 00:34:19.640
He keeps calling me.
and he left me a really long message.

528
00:34:19.720 --> 00:34:21.930
- Who… Who keeps calling?
- The grandad.

529
00:34:24.640 --> 00:34:25.810
The boy's grandad.

530
00:34:27.560 --> 00:34:28.860
Rohaan. the…

531
00:34:30.070 --> 00:34:31.150
Yeah.

532
00:34:33.230 --> 00:34:36.070
And the worst thing is.
I don't understand what he's saying.

533
00:34:37.070 --> 00:34:39.490
'cause it's all in Punjabi. so…

534
00:34:39.580 --> 00:34:41.490
You want me to listen? I can translate.

535
00:34:43.120 --> 00:34:44.120
Can you?

536
00:34:44.960 --> 00:34:46.460
Yes. please.

537
00:34:51.710 --> 00:34:53.920
Hello? Hello.

538
00:34:57.840 --> 00:35:00.010
Yeah. He's…

539
00:35:01.600 --> 00:35:03.640
Yeah. he's… he's glad you came.

540
00:35:11.320 --> 00:35:12.320
Yeah.

541
00:35:14.190 --> 00:35:15.360
Yeah. he's…

542
00:35:17.860 --> 00:35:20.530
He's… He's just feeling really sad.

543
00:35:24.160 --> 00:35:25.330
Yeah.

544
00:35:31.340 --> 00:35:32.710
You're gonna get me going now.

545
00:35:34.840 --> 00:35:35.840
Thank you.

546
00:35:36.920 --> 00:35:37.930
Thank you.

547
00:35:43.850 --> 00:35:44.850
Anyway…

548
00:35:46.100 --> 00:35:47.270
Look. it's…

549
00:35:48.480 --> 00:35:50.850
It's just a couple of days with Hegarty.

550
00:35:53.150 --> 00:35:56.400
And if I can just get the bastard
that killed Rohaan…

551
00:36:00.490 --> 00:36:01.530
All right.

552
00:36:02.410 --> 00:36:03.490
Do what you gotta do.

553
00:36:05.660 --> 00:36:07.450
Just don't forget. yeah?

554
00:36:07.540 --> 00:36:10.210
Don't forget who you're dealing with.

555
00:36:13.340 --> 00:36:14.340
No chance.

556
00:37:34.080 --> 00:37:36.250
Get the fuck out of my house!

557
00:37:50.180 --> 00:37:51.270
Police. police!

558
00:37:53.230 --> 00:37:55.150
Where is he? Is he here?

559
00:37:56.690 --> 00:37:58.270
How'd you get here so quick?

560
00:38:01.860 --> 00:38:03.450
- Kim.
- JP.

561
00:38:04.110 --> 00:38:05.570
- Boss.
- How's the mother?

562
00:38:05.660 --> 00:38:07.490
She's. yeah. she's fine.

563
00:38:07.570 --> 00:38:10.200
- Where's our boy?
- He went out the back. Traveling on foot.

564
00:38:12.040 --> 00:38:15.210
Okay. JP with me.
Let's go. Let's find him.

565
00:38:15.290 --> 00:38:17.330
Do we put out a general alert?

566
00:38:18.040 --> 00:38:19.500
God. no. We'll be here all night.

567
00:38:20.090 --> 00:38:24.090
- Oi! Keith. Keith!
- Let's go. Let's find the little shit.

568
00:38:25.880 --> 00:38:27.760
Finn. get over to Park Hill Road.

569
00:38:27.850 --> 00:38:30.430
- See if he's heading for the station.
- Copy that.

570
00:38:52.240 --> 00:38:53.750
Got you.

571
00:38:54.290 --> 00:38:55.330
Oi! Oi!

572
00:38:55.410 --> 00:38:57.210
Subject identified! On foot. heading…

573
00:38:58.040 --> 00:39:01.040
No. he's going south
off the high street down Markham Road.

574
00:39:01.550 --> 00:39:02.880
He's heading for the canal.

575
00:39:06.090 --> 00:39:07.760
You can catch him up
if you take King Street.

576
00:39:18.940 --> 00:39:20.940
Fucking hell.

577
00:39:26.610 --> 00:39:27.950
Cut him off!

578
00:39:36.750 --> 00:39:39.960
Pursuing subject east
up the canal towards Homerton.

579
00:39:41.250 --> 00:39:42.710
Fuck. Shit!

580
00:39:42.790 --> 00:39:43.880
Oi!

581
00:39:46.090 --> 00:39:47.300
Fucking stop!

582
00:39:50.760 --> 00:39:51.760
Oi!

583
00:40:42.770 --> 00:40:44.150
Stay there.

584
00:40:47.990 --> 00:40:49.070
I went back.

585
00:40:49.150 --> 00:40:50.280
Shut up.

586
00:40:50.360 --> 00:40:52.110
He fell in. I… I got him out. I…

587
00:40:52.200 --> 00:40:53.620
Shut up. you hear?

588
00:40:53.700 --> 00:40:56.330
D… Dan. I went back and I got him out.

589
00:40:56.410 --> 00:40:57.450
Shut up!

590
00:40:58.450 --> 00:41:00.830
Don't you ever say my name again.
you hear?

590
